<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1309440 size-large" src="https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-1024x691.jpg" alt="Facebook’s Libra 2020 launch plan still unclear – Board member" width="640" height="432" srcset="https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-1024x691.jpg 1024w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-300x203.jpg 300w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-768x518.jpg 768w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-58x39.jpg 58w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-260x176.jpg 260w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-193x130.jpg 193w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-115x77.jpg 115w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6-560x378.jpg 560w, https://www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/download-6.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" /> Facebook’s Libra project has no solid strategy yet for how or where it will be introduced in 2020, a board member of the body overseeing the hotly-anticipated cryptocurrency told Reuters on Thursday. “Libra is on track to launch in 2020, however, the scope of the roll-out depends on talks with regulators,’’ said Patrick Ellis, one of five board members for the Geneva-based Libra Association that will issue and govern the digital currency. According to Ellis, at this stage, there is no strategy set in stone for the markets or the product, or how it will actually get rolled out. The prospect of Libra being used by Facebook’s (FB.O) near-2.4 billion users has drawn fierce scrutiny from authorities around the world, who are nervous that it could alter the global financial landscape. Vanguard News Nigeria Widespread adoption of Facebook's proposed "Libra" cryptocurrency could harm the European Central Bank's ability to manage the eurozone economy and threaten the euro itself, a top official said Monday. September 2, 2019 In "Technology" US regulators on Wednesday slapped a record $5 billion fine on Facebook for privacy violations in a wide-ranging settlement that calls for revamping privacy controls and oversight at the social network. July 24, 2019 In "News" Facebook Chief Executive Officer, Mark Zuckerberg is expected to appear before the United States Congress today to defend "Facebook's Impact on the Financial Services and Housing Sectors," but there are reports the interview will be more focused on Facebook's "Project Libra". Project Libra was introduced by Facebook earlier in June.… October 23, 2019 In "Foreign"